<br>
 I can follow people's misunderstanding of the plant we call marijuna. I live with it everyday. I am not a violent person; I have never hurt anyone in the pursuit of my religion. But I am persecuted for my sacrament by laws that have no basis as related to me. I work, have children, own a home ,have a degree and pay taxes like everyone else. I hurt no one to further my belief system nor do I impose it on others. My religion is one of tolerance and mutual understanding. So I see your side of the argument clearly .<br>
<br>
Yes it’s an intoxicant, to me that's the only argument that has any validity for keeping it out of the hands of the masses, if you are intoxicated all the time you cannot move forward with what’s right for you and society.  Sober clarity is necessary if only to provide direction and motivation. This is undeniably true, regardless the intoxicant of choosing or which religion you follow.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of Fuctard stoner DOOODZ out there and the world would probably be a better place without them getting high. But we are not all driven by the same motivation some seek greater things, as corny as it sounds some seek &quot;Enlightenment”. For all those people I say &quot;Much Love &quot;. For all the others that don’t relate to what I’m saying I say “Much Love and Understanding” <br>
<br>
Ire ,<br>
<br>
