LOL no dreads here, I’m a comber. I meditate every day, just as many pray, but this article isn’t based in usable fact really. It has some historical points but the following of the Ras Tafari is very different than stated and doesn’t fall along such divided lines as the link may suggest. <br>
<br>
And what makes one a true Rasta anyway? That’s a good question. I know some that are pure vegans and I know some that eat meat and still practice ritual, I know some that follow Ras Tafari openly and others that believe in it, in a &quot;ZEN kind of way&quot; and only practice meditation in private. Its really what you believe in your heart that makes you spiritual in any way shape or form in my opinion.<br>
<br>
 I truly don’t come here advocating Marijuana usage or use my religion to say it’s ok to be a stoner. I hope only to pose a different point of view  to that of the always harped on <br>
“Dude Im soo Stoned “ mentality of many users. And ask people to look at the other side of the coin.<br>
<br>
Many other religions use weed though in there practice of spiritualism just the most noted is Rastafarianism. Due to its association with Bob Marley and 60's movement.<br>
<br>
Most people don’t realize it but Buddhism also practices the sacrament as do many Native American cultures. <br>
<br>
